Sunburst Front Door with transom and brass silhouette sunrise in front to give the transom the look of having fanlights.
description: This is the front door to Danny and Stency Wegman's house. It weighs about 400 lbs. Inside of the door is a welded steel framework. The transom-light is covered by a sculpted and hammered brass plate.

title: New Beginnings with Strawberries
description:
This was painted in a coffee shop. A mom and her little girl stopped to see what I was doing and I gave her the freedom to paint some colors on it. Her name ( Riley Vinci ) is noted on the bottom right of the art.
This piece is about restarting. Strawberries are an Iroquois symbol for New Beginnings because they are the first fruit in the Spring. There are eight of them because the Hebrew meaning of the number 8 is New Beginnings. And the Infinity symbol speaks of a path called the Way by Jesus. His way is full of New Beginnings every morning. The mountain climber is being helped by a guardian angel and the Holy Spirit to a fresh view at a new height.
